CSS : cascalading style sheet
CSS is all about rules
rules : 
selector {
    propreties:values;
}

Ways to include a CSS style:
    1/ Inline (not a good idea) ex:<h1 style="color : purple">Hello World</h1>
    2/ Style element (not recommended) exemple : <style>h2{color:violet;}</style>
    3/ External StyleSheet:
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="app_style.css">
        link is always in the head !

Different propreties :
    color : change the color of the text
    background-color : change the color of the background

Color Systems :
Named color : Simplest to use but also the most limited. (about 140 colors)
RGB : Additive, each channel go from 0 to 255 (255 = maxed out, 0 = nothing)
Hexadecimal : Same as RGB but represented as Hexadecimal (#ffff00)
To search a certains color, just go look at a color picker on internet

Conseil: ALWAYS CHECK ';' ! 

<!-- Text attribute -->
text-align : centre|right|left
font-weight : normal | bold | 400 |
text-decoration : blue wavy underline | overline | none
line-height : normal | 2.5 | 150% | 32 px
letter-spacing : 2.5 px | ...

font-size: 12 px | % | em 

pixels are not recommended for responsive website !
font-family : Arial, sans-serif, georgia; (the second is backup if the font is not available)



